description: The Department of Transportation is responsible for planning and coordinating federal transportation projects. It also sets safety regulations for all major modes of transportation.

departments.description: The FAA works to ensure that all air travel is safe.
departments.name: Federal Aviation Administration
departments.notes: This office has additional FOIA contact information that can be found by visiting its website.

departments.description: The Federal Highway Administration supports state and local government in the design, construction, and maintenance of the highway system.
departments.name: Federal Highway Administration

departments.description: The Federal Railroad Administration is charged with creating and enforcing rail safety regulations, administering rail funding, and researching rail improvement strategies and technologies.

address_lines: FOIA/PA Contact, Office of the Chief Counsel

departments.name: Federal Railroad Administration

departments.description: The Federal Transit Administration seeks to improve public transportation by assisting state and local governments with planning, implementation, and financing of public transportation projects.
departments.name: Federal Transit Administration

departments.description: The FMCSA provides information about your rights when moving across state lines (interstate moves). Consumers should submit household goods commercial complaints or dangerous safety violations involving a commercial truck or bus to this agency.
departments.name: Federal Motor Carrier Safety Administration

departments.description: The National Highway Traffic Safety Administration (NHTSA) is responsible for reducing deaths, injuries and economic losses resulting from motor vehicle crashes. The agency investigates safety defects in motor vehicles, sets and enforces fuel economy standards, helps states and local communities reduce the threat of drunk drivers, promotes the use of safety belts, child safety seats and air bags, investigates odometer fraud, establishes and enforces vehicle anti-theft regulations, conducts research on driver behavior and traffic safety, and provides consumer information on motor vehicle safety topics.
departments.name: National Highway Traffic Safety Administration

departments.description: Part of the Department of Transportation, the Maritime Commission works to ensure the health of the U.S. merchant marine. The Maritime Administration also works to improve port efficiency, and to maintain an adequate ship building and repair infrastructure.

address_lines: FOIA Officer, Division of Legislation and Regulations

departments.name: Maritime Administration

departments.description: The Pipeline and Hazardous Materials Safety Administration regulates the transport of hazardous materials.
departments.name: Pipeline and Hazardous Materials Safety Administration

departments.description: Working in concert with its Canadian counterpart, the Saint Lawrence Seaway Development Corporation works to operate and maintain a safe, reliable, efficient waterway between the Great Lakes and the Atlantic Ocean.
departments.name: Saint Lawrence Seaway Development Corporation

departments.description: The Surface Transportation Board regulates and decides disputes involving railroad rates, railroad mergers or line sales, and certain other transportation matters.
departments.name: Surface Transportation Board

name: Department of Transportation
